The paper deals with distributed resource allocation problems in dynamic topology networks, which are typically studied in the Distributed Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The use of finite messaging passing suggests a focus on Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as well. The study of conflict minimization and enumeration of protocols suggests a focus on Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Game Theory (cs.GT). Finally, the mention of a sufficient condition for conflict-free allocation suggests a focus on Systems and Control (cs.SY).
